Some file types, like ".exe" for example, are powerful because they make a computer do things

Those things could be bad for you or your computer

For them types od dile, the send request will be blocked by the server

Putting someone on your DCC Allow list tells the server that they are someone you trust, that you allow them to send you files which would usually be blocked

Your DCC Allow list is cleared when you finish your session. If you connect to the network again, you will have to re-add these trusted people
